{
  "text": "Biologically, experiments have been done using these molecules exogenously to enhance tooth movement both in animal experiments and humans. Examples of these molecules are prostaglandin E, cytokines that include lymphocytes and monocyte-derived factors, receptor activator of nuclear factor kappa B ligand, and macrophage colony-stimulating factor. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] The effects of cytokines, osteocalcins, prostaglandins, Vitamin D 3 , and parathyroid hormone and relaxin have also been evaluated.",
  "citation_candidates": [
